  missing DATABASE_URL in the Prisma schema, a critical Next.js security
  vulnerability (CVE-2025-66478) requiring an upgrade to Next.js 16, subsequent
  ESLint configuration adjustments due to next lint removal, and finally,
  lazy-loading the Prisma client to prevent build-time database connection
  errors. The agent also updated outdated e2e tests and corrected the progress
  bar logic. Ultimately, all GitHub Actions and Vercel deployments are now
  passing, and the PR is ready to merge."
